Sir Alex Ferguson has told Manchester United to sign John McGinn, according to Kevin Phillips. When asked whether Aston Villa have missed the injured Scotsman, he told Football Insider: “Yeah, he’s a huge miss. “You don’t get Alex Ferguson telling United to go and sign someone if you’re not a good player. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “I think he’s a massive loss. Again, [Tom] Heaton out, Wesley out, McGinn – these things happen to you when you’re at the bottom of the league, unfortunately, but I think the positive for Dean Smith is he signed enough players in the summer to try and cope with it. “John McGinn, when you lose one of your best players, if not your best player apart from [Jack] Grealish, it’s going to hurt you.”